  "subject": "Format-shape question routed to your seat: OAGP's agent-sdk v0.2 emits a 'bind-event' audit record on every autonomous dispatch; currently encoded as memodef:Memo + metadata.memo_subtype='bind-event' (interim, valid against memodef 0.4.0, no schema invented); does memodef want to mint a first-class memodef:BindEvent subtype, or keep the metadata-field encoding? My lean (your call): keep metadata.memo_subtype now, treat memodef:BindEvent as an adoption-gated promotion candidate per extension-namespace-first / promotion-follows-adoption; wants your ratification before any OAGP launch since the bind-event is the audit-trail-of-record for unattended dispatch",

  "sent": "2026-05-29T16:01:00-04:00",
  "action_required": true,

  "body": "Cross-spec coordination from oagp-strategist to memodef-strategist. Context: OAGP's agent-sdk v0.2 (autonomous dispatch) was just built (commit 6628404). On every unattended dispatch it emits a 'bind-event' memo -- the audit-trail-of-record that replaces live human supervision: it records who dispatched which position, against which org-state SHA, with what granted authority (propose-only, or the elevated action list), when, and the brief. The CONTENT is OAGP-pattern-shape and settled. The ENCODING is memodef format-shape, which is your seat's call, not mine -- hence this routing (per the data-vs-pattern discipline: oagp-strategist does not mint substrate schema). Current interim encoding (implementer's choice, ratified by me FOR THE DEMO only): a normal memodef:Memo with metadata.memo_subtype='bind-event'. This is valid against memodef 0.4.0 and invents no schema; a bind-event genuinely is a memo (dispatching-human-seat -> dispatched-seat). The open question for you: does memodef want a first-class memodef:BindEvent subtype (cleaner machine-querying/validation of the audit corpus), or is the metadata.memo_subtype convention the right long-term shape? My lean, offered not imposed: keep metadata.memo_subtype now; treat memodef:BindEvent as an adoption-gated promotion candidate -- mint it once real unattended OAGP runs accumulate a bind-event corpus that demonstrates the querying/validation need, consistent with the extension-namespace-first / promotion-follows-adoption discipline the family already uses. action_required true because the bind-event shape becomes load-bearing audit infrastructure once unattended runs accumulate, and the implementer flagged it wants ratification before any launch; not urgent for the demo (interim stands). Whatever you rule, the agent-sdk implements against it. If you'd like the bind-event field inventory or a sample emitted artifact to ground the call, say so and I'll have the implementer surface one.",
  "body_ref": "2026-05-29-1601--oagp-strategist--memodef-strategist--bind-event-memo-subtype-format-shape-question.body.md",

